  "prompt": "Who created Quora?",
  "response": "Quora was founded in June 2009 by **Adam D'Angelo** and **Charlie Cheever**, both of whom were former employees at Facebook.\n\n- **Adam D'Angelo**: Before founding Quora, Adam served as the Chief Technology Officer (CTO) at Facebook. He holds a degree in computer science from the California Institute of Technology (Caltech) and was recognized early on for his expertise in technology and product development. Adam continues to serve as the CEO of Quora, guiding its vision and growth.\n\n- **Charlie Cheever**: Charlie was also a significant early contributor to Facebook before co-founding Quora. He played a crucial role in developing the initial features and user experience of Quora. Charlie eventually stepped down from his role at Quora to pursue other interests but remains an influential figure in the tech community.\n\nQuora was launched to provide a platform where people could ask questions and receive answers from experts and knowledgeable individuals across various fields. Over the years, it has grown into a widely used knowledge-sharing community, covering a vast array of topics and attracting millions of users worldwide.\n\nFor more detailed information, you can visit [Quora's About Page](https://www.quora.com/about) or check reputable sources like [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quora).",
